const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'J$67,500-107,000', annual: 'J$810,000-1,284,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'J$92,500-143,000', annual: 'J$1,110,000-1,716,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'J$125,000-192,000', annual: 'J$1,500,000-2,304,000' },
  { category: 'Local Private Insurance', monthly: 'J$35,000-60,000/mo', annual: 'J$420,000-720,000' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'J$100,000-200,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Jamaica 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Jamaica. Caribbean culture, stunning beaches, English-speaking, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Jamaica"
  subheadline="Jamaica offers vibrant Caribbean culture, stunning natural beauty, English language, and welcoming atmosphere—an affordable retirement option for those who understand both benefits and challenges."
  heroImage="/images/countries/jamaica-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Jamaica</h2>
  <p>
    Jamaica offers Caribbean culture, beautiful beaches, Blue Mountains, and English language. For those with Jamaican heritage or seeking affordable Caribbean retirement, Jamaica provides character that more polished destinations lack. Understand security considerations realistically.
  </p>

  <p>
    Montego Bay has tourism infrastructure and expat communities. Ocho Rios offers resort living. Negril provides beach lifestyle. Kingston has capital amenities but security concerns. North coast communities popular with retirees. Inner cities of Kingston and some rural areas require caution.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving; private options available</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> J$250,000-500,000/month (~$1,600-3,200); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round; hurricane risk</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Vibrant; musical; resilient</li>
      <li><strong>Diaspora:</strong> Large Jamaican diaspora returns for retirement</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Jamaica Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Jamaica healthcare is improving—University Hospital of the West Indies in Kingston is the main teaching hospital. Private facilities include Medical Associates, Andrews Memorial, and Hospiten in Montego Bay. Quality varies significantly between public and private sectors.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private hospitals provide good care for many conditions. Complex cases may require evacuation to Miami (90-minute flight). Public system is under-resourced. Medical tourism from the US growing—some specialists are excellent. Insurance covering private care essential.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Private Care Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Public healthcare in Jamaica is limited—private facilities are significantly better. Ensure insurance covers private hospitals in Jamaica plus evacuation to Miami for complex conditions. Hospiten Montego Bay is JCI-accredited and popular with expats.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Jamaica has options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Returning Resident</h3>
  <p>
    For Jamaican citizens returning home. Most straightforward option for diaspora retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>Indefinite Leave to Remain</h3>
  <p>
    For those with means to support themselves. Demonstrate income/assets. Application through immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Work Permit (Self-Employed)</h3>
  <p>
    For those starting businesses. Can work for semi-retired entrepreneurs.
  </p>

  <h3>Visitor Visa/Stamp</h3>
  <p>
    Many nationalities receive 30-90 days on arrival. Extensions possible but not for permanent retirement.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Jamaica:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Indefinite leave:</strong> Health insurance recommended, may be required</li>
    <li><strong>Practical necessity:</strong> Private coverage essential for quality care</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Miami coverage for complex conditions</li>
    <li><strong>Local options:</strong> Available but limited for seniors</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Jamaica</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with private Jamaica and US coverage recommended. Local insurers (Sagicor) may have age limits or restrictions. Ensure evacuation to Miami included. Caribbean-excluding-US plans risky for serious conditions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Jamaica, coverage with Miami/US access essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Jamaica</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Caribbean + US coverage, excellent network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), Americas coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Sagicor:</strong> Major regional insurer, but age limits</li>
    <li><strong>Hospiten network:</strong> International chain with Jamaica presence</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with Caribbean and US benefits.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Jamaica (note currency fluctuation):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Local for routine:</strong> Sagicor for regular care if eligible</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Reduce monthly premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> Caribbean-focused options exist</li>
    <li><strong>US-excluding:</strong> Cheaper but not recommended for seniors</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Jamaican-American Returning, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> US$3,000/month pension. Returning resident. Ocho Rios.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Americas coverage. Medicare for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~J$85,000/month. Coming home; US healthcare backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Retiree, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £2,800/month pension. Indefinite leave. Montego Bay.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with UK and Caribbean coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~J$110,000/month. Tropical retirement; UK healthcare if needed.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Canadian Snowbird, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> C$4,000/month pension. Winter months only. Negril area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care travel plan + maintain provincial coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~J$50,000/month for Jamaica time. Caribbean winters; Canadian healthcare for rest of year.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Jamaica safe for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Mixed—tourist areas and north coast communities are generally safe. Kingston inner city and some rural areas have security concerns. Most expat retirees live in resort areas or gated communities without issues. Research specific areas; exercise urban caution.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How is Jamaica healthcare for seniors?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Improving but variable—private facilities are good; public is limited. Hospiten Montego Bay has international standards. Complex conditions may require Miami evacuation (90 minutes). Plan for private care; don't rely on public system.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about hurricanes?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Jamaica is in hurricane zone—June to November is season. Major hurricanes occur periodically. Insurance should cover weather-related evacuation. Some retirees leave during peak hurricane months.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is cost of living affordable?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate—cheaper than Barbados or Bahamas, more expensive than Central America. Imported goods costly; local food affordable. Budget J$250,000-400,000/month (~$1,600-2,500) for comfortable living outside resort areas.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with Jamaica coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Jamaica authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
